Measure type: [123] Non preferential tariff quota under end-use
Order number: [01] + 11.00 EUR / Tonne | [04] + 0.15 EUR + % or amount / Decatonne, corrected according to polarisation
Measure components: Condition [Q1] Presentation of an endorsed certificate/licence : Document [Y] Action [27] Apply the mentioned duty : ||Condition [C2] Presentation of a certificate/licence/document : Document [L] Action [27] Apply the mentioned duty : ||Condition [B3] Presentation of a certificate/licence/document : Document [U] Action [27] Apply the mentioned duty : ||Condition [H4] Presentation of a certificate/licence/document : Document [N] Action [27] Apply the mentioned duty : ||Condition [C5] Presentation of a certificate/licence/document : Action [07] Measure not applicable : ||Condition [Q6] Presentation of an endorsed certificate/licence : Action [07] Measure not applicable : ||Condition [H7] Presentation of a certificate/licence/document : Action [08] Declared subheading not allowed : ||Condition [B8] Presentation of a certificate/licence/document : Action [07] Measure not applicable :
Conditions: CD478: (Conditions) Eligibility to benefit from this tariff quota is subject to the production of a certificate of origin meeting the conditions laid down in Article 57 of Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) 2015/2447 and of an import licence obtained in accordance with the conditions laid down in Regulation (EC) No 891/2009 (OJ L 254). | EU001: (End use) The relief from or reduction of customs duties shall be subject to the conditions laid down in the relevant provisions of the European Union with a view to customs control of the use of such goods (see Article 254 of Regulation (EU) No 952/2013 of the European Parliament and of the Council (OJ L 269, 10. 10. 2013, p. 1)). | TM696: (Taric Measure) Where the polarimetric reading of the imported raw sugar departs from 96 degrees, the rate of 11 Euros/98 Euros per tonne shall be increased or reduced, as appropriate, by 0.14|% per tenth of a degree of difference established.
